Last week, various branches at the tax collection agency were shut down, with employees calling for an 11.4% increase. JOHANNESBURG - The Public Servants Association (PSA) has reached an agreement with the South African Revenue Service (Sars) following a wage strike. Last week, various branches at the tax collection agency were shut down, with employees calling for an 11.4% increase. Sars and the union have agreed on a three-year deal which includes an 8% hike for the first 12 months. The PSA’s Tahir Maepa said: “In terms of this particular agreement, we managed to agree on an 8% increase for year one, and a CPI plus 2% for year two and three for our members.” However, there's no word yet on a deal between the agency and Nehawu.